# Copy to .env and edit. Both compose files read it.
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# .env is in .gitignore's blast radius via .dockerignore for the image, but it
# is a plain file on your host — if you put MUX_PEPPER in it, that file is now
# as sensitive as your password database. Read the last section before you do.


# --- MUX_PORT -------------------------------------------------------------
# Host port the gateway is published on. Only the host side; the container
# always listens on 8080.
#
#   MUX_PORT=8080     http://localhost:8080
#   MUX_PORT=80       standard HTTP, needs a privileged port on Linux
#
# Behind a reverse proxy on the same host, also change the port mapping in
# docker-compose.yml to bind loopback only, so the gateway is not reachable
# except through the proxy:
#
#   - "127.0.0.1:${MUX_PORT:-8080}:8080"
#
MUX_PORT=8080


# --- TZ -------------------------------------------------------------------
# The container's timezone, in tzdata form (Area/City). Every app child process
# inherits it. This is not cosmetic: workoutt's notification scheduler builds
# reminder instants in local time, so the wrong value here sends every reminder
# at the wrong hour, correctly, forever.
#
#   TZ=America/Halifax
#
TZ=UTC


# --- MUX_PEPPER -----------------------------------------------------------
# THE DANGEROUS ONE. Read all of this.
#
# The pepper is a server-wide secret mixed into every password and recovery
# passphrase hash before Argon2id. It is what makes a stolen mux.db useless on
# its own: without the pepper an attacker cannot verify a single password guess
# — not slowly, not expensively, at all.
#
# Leave it EMPTY and the gateway generates one on first boot and stores it at
# data/pepper.key, inside the volume. That works, and it is the right default.
# Its weakness is that a backup of ./data then contains both the hashes and the
# key that protects them, which is a backup with no pepper in it.
#
# Setting it here keeps the pepper OUT of the data volume entirely — the
# environment is checked before the key file, and pepper.key is never created.
# That is the point of having the variable: ./data can then be backed up
# normally, and the secret lives wherever you keep secrets.
#
# Format: base64, decoding to at least 16 bytes. Generate one with
#
#   openssl rand -base64 32
#
# NOW THE PART THAT BITES.
#
#   * Changing this value invalidates EVERY password and EVERY recovery
#     passphrase on the system, immediately and silently. Nobody can log in.
#     Not the users, not you. The login page just says the credentials are
#     wrong, because as far as the hash is concerned they are.
#   * Losing it does the same thing permanently. There is no recovery
#     procedure — not a difficult one, none. The only remedy is resetting every
#     account by hand, and if your own admin account is among them that means
#     editing SQLite directly.
#   * Setting it on a system that has ALREADY booted with a generated
#     pepper.key is the same as changing it. Migrating means re-hashing every
#     credential, which nothing here does. Decide before first boot.
#   * Emptying it again on a system that was using it is also the same thing:
#     the gateway will not find pepper.key, will generate a NEW random one, and
#     will look for all the world like it started up fine.
#
# So: set it before the first sign-up, or never. Store it somewhere you would
# store a root password — a password manager entry, a secrets manager, systemd
# credentials — and specifically NOT next to your ./data backups.
#
# MUX_PEPPER=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# MUX_IMAGE — which published image docker-compose.yml pulls.
#
# Only needed if this repository lives somewhere other than the default in
# docker-compose.yml, or to pin a release instead of tracking :latest. GHCR
# names are always lowercase, whatever case the GitHub org uses.
#
#   MUX_IMAGE=ghcr.io/kieran-s-artisnal-slop-factory/muxerr:v1.0.0
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#MUX_IMAGE=ghcr.io/kieran-s-artisnal-slop-factory/muxerr:latest
